stream
BT /F2 18 Tf 54 738.00 Td (Recordkeeper Backup And Recovery Guide) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 697.00 Td (This guide explains how to configure automatic PostgreSQL backups for the LAN) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 683.00 Td (deployment and how to restore the database if records are accidentally or maliciously) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 669.00 Td (deleted.) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 647.00 Td (The commands below assume the production database is:) Tj ET
BT /F3 8.8 Tf 54 617.00 Td (recordkeeper) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 589.00 Td (and the database URL is:) Tj ET
BT /F3 8.8 Tf 54 559.00 Td (postgresql://postgres:postgres@localhost:5432/recordkeeper) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 531.00 Td (If your server uses a different PostgreSQL username, password, host, port, or database) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 517.00 Td (name, replace the URL everywhere in this guide.) Tj ET
BT /F2 13 Tf 54 487.00 Td (1. What The Backup System Will Do) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 456.00 Td (The recommended setup will:) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 434.00 Td (- create one database backup every day at a fixed time) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 420.00 Td (- store backups in `/opt/recordkeeper/backups`) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 406.00 Td (- keep only the latest 7 daily backups) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 392.00 Td (- write a small log file so backup success or failure can be checked) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 378.00 Td (- allow recovery by restoring one selected backup into PostgreSQL) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 356.00 Td (This backs up the PostgreSQL database only. It does not back up operating system) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 342.00 Td (files, Nginx config, app build files, or uploaded documents if those are added later.) Tj ET
BT /F2 13 Tf 54 312.00 Td (2. Create The Backup Folder) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 281.00 Td (Run this on the Ubuntu LAN server:) Tj ET
BT /F3 8.8 Tf 54 251.00 Td (sudo mkdir -p /opt/recordkeeper/backups) Tj ET
BT /F3 8.8 Tf 54 239.00 Td (sudo chown -R $USER:$USER /opt/recordkeeper/backups) Tj ET
BT /F3 8.8 Tf 54 227.00 Td (chmod 700 /opt/recordkeeper/backups) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 199.00 Td (The `chmod 700` command restricts access to the backup folder because database backups) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 185.00 Td (may contain sensitive office data.) Tj ET
BT /F2 13 Tf 54 155.00 Td (3. Create The Backup Script) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 124.00 Td (Create a script file:) Tj ET
BT /F3 8.8 Tf 54 94.00 Td (nano /opt/recordkeeper/backup-recordkeeper.sh) Tj ET
endstream
endobj
5 0 obj
<< /Length 2252 >>
stream
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 738.00 Td (Paste this:) Tj ET
BT /F3 8.8 Tf 54 708.00 Td (#!/bin/bash) Tj ET
BT /F3 8.8 Tf 54 696.00 Td (set -euo pipefail) Tj ET
BT /F3 8.8 Tf 54 684.00 Td () Tj ET
BT /F3 8.8 Tf 54 672.00 Td (BACKUP_DIR="/opt/recordkeeper/backups") Tj ET
BT /F3 8.8 Tf 54 660.00 Td (DB_URL="postgresql://postgres:postgres@localhost:5432/recordkeeper") Tj ET
BT /F3 8.8 Tf 54 648.00 Td (DATE="$\(date +%F_%H-%M-%S\)") Tj ET
BT /F3 8.8 Tf 54 636.00 Td (BACKUP_FILE="$BACKUP_DIR/recordkeeper_$DATE.sql") Tj ET
BT /F3 8.8 Tf 54 624.00 Td (LOG_FILE="$BACKUP_DIR/backup.log") Tj ET
BT /F3 8.8 Tf 54 612.00 Td () Tj ET
BT /F3 8.8 Tf 54 600.00 Td (mkdir -p "$BACKUP_DIR") Tj ET
BT /F3 8.8 Tf 54 588.00 Td () Tj ET
BT /F3 8.8 Tf 54 576.00 Td (echo "[$\(date '+%F %T'\)] Starting backup: $BACKUP_FILE" >> "$LOG_FILE") Tj ET
BT /F3 8.8 Tf 54 564.00 Td () Tj ET
BT /F3 8.8 Tf 54 552.00 Td (pg_dump "$DB_URL" > "$BACKUP_FILE") Tj ET
BT /F3 8.8 Tf 54 540.00 Td () Tj ET
BT /F3 8.8 Tf 54 528.00 Td (gzip "$BACKUP_FILE") Tj ET
BT /F3 8.8 Tf 54 516.00 Td () Tj ET
BT /F3 8.8 Tf 54 504.00 Td (find "$BACKUP_DIR" -name "recordkeeper_*.sql.gz" -type f -mtime +6 -delete) Tj ET
BT /F3 8.8 Tf 54 492.00 Td () Tj ET
BT /F3 8.8 Tf 54 480.00 Td (echo "[$\(date '+%F %T'\)] Backup completed successfully" >> "$LOG_FILE") Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 452.00 Td (Save and close the file.) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 430.00 Td (Make the script executable:) Tj ET
BT /F3 8.8 Tf 54 400.00 Td (chmod +x /opt/recordkeeper/backup-recordkeeper.sh) Tj ET
BT /F2 13 Tf 54 364.00 Td (4. Test The Backup Script Manually) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 333.00 Td (Before scheduling it, run it once:) Tj ET
BT /F3 8.8 Tf 54 303.00 Td (/opt/recordkeeper/backup-recordkeeper.sh) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 275.00 Td (Check that a backup file was created:) Tj ET
BT /F3 8.8 Tf 54 245.00 Td (ls -lh /opt/recordkeeper/backups) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 217.00 Td (You should see a file like:) Tj ET
BT /F3 8.8 Tf 54 187.00 Td (recordkeeper_2026-06-24_20-00-00.sql.gz) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 159.00 Td (Check the log:) Tj ET
BT /F3 8.8 Tf 54 129.00 Td (tail -n 20 /opt/recordkeeper/backups/backup.log) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 101.00 Td (If the script fails, fix the database URL or PostgreSQL permissions before continuing.) Tj ET
endstream
endobj
6 0 obj
<< /Length 1938 >>
stream
BT /F2 13 Tf 54 730.00 Td (5. Schedule Daily Automatic Backups) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 699.00 Td (Open the current user's crontab:) Tj ET
BT /F3 8.8 Tf 54 669.00 Td (crontab -e) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 641.00 Td (Add this line to run the backup every day at 8:00 PM:) Tj ET
BT /F3 8.8 Tf 54 611.00 Td (0 20 * * * /opt/recordkeeper/backup-recordkeeper.sh >> /opt/recordkeeper/backu) Tj ET
BT /F3 8.8 Tf 54 599.00 Td (ps/cron.log 2>&1) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 571.00 Td (Save and close.) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 549.00 Td (To choose a different time, change the first two values:) Tj ET
BT /F3 8.8 Tf 54 519.00 Td (minute hour * * *) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 491.00 Td (Examples:) Tj ET
BT /F3 8.8 Tf 54 461.00 Td (# Every day at 1:30 PM) Tj ET
BT /F3 8.8 Tf 54 449.00 Td (30 13 * * * /opt/recordkeeper/backup-recordkeeper.sh >> /opt/recordkeeper/back) Tj ET
BT /F3 8.8 Tf 54 437.00 Td (ups/cron.log 2>&1) Tj ET
BT /F3 8.8 Tf 54 425.00 Td () Tj ET
BT /F3 8.8 Tf 54 413.00 Td (# Every day at 11:00 PM) Tj ET
BT /F3 8.8 Tf 54 401.00 Td (0 23 * * * /opt/recordkeeper/backup-recordkeeper.sh >> /opt/recordkeeper/backu) Tj ET
BT /F3 8.8 Tf 54 389.00 Td (ps/cron.log 2>&1) Tj ET
BT /F2 13 Tf 54 353.00 Td (6. Confirm The Schedule Is Installed) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 322.00 Td (Run:) Tj ET
BT /F3 8.8 Tf 54 292.00 Td (crontab -l) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 264.00 Td (Confirm the backup line is visible.) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 242.00 Td (After the scheduled time passes, check:) Tj ET
BT /F3 8.8 Tf 54 212.00 Td (ls -lh /opt/recordkeeper/backups) Tj ET
BT /F3 8.8 Tf 54 200.00 Td (tail -n 50 /opt/recordkeeper/backups/backup.log) Tj ET
BT /F3 8.8 Tf 54 188.00 Td (tail -n 50 /opt/recordkeeper/backups/cron.log) Tj ET
BT /F2 13 Tf 54 152.00 Td (7. How Retention Works) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 121.00 Td (This line in the script removes old backups:) Tj ET
BT /F3 8.8 Tf 54 91.00 Td (find "$BACKUP_DIR" -name "recordkeeper_*.sql.gz" -type f -mtime +6 -delete) Tj ET
endstream
endobj
7 0 obj
<< /Length 2704 >>
stream
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 738.00 Td (Because the backup runs daily, this keeps roughly the latest 7 daily backups.) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 716.00 Td (If you want to keep 14 days instead, change `+6` to `+13`.) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 694.00 Td (If you want to keep 30 days, change `+6` to `+29`.) Tj ET
BT /F2 13 Tf 54 664.00 Td (8. Recommended Extra Protection) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 633.00 Td (Daily backups are helpful, but they are still on the same server. For better) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 619.00 Td (protection:) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 597.00 Td (- copy backups to another computer or external drive regularly) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 583.00 Td (- keep at least one weekly backup outside the server) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 569.00 Td (- restrict access to `/opt/recordkeeper/backups`) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 555.00 Td (- restrict who has admin access inside the app) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 541.00 Td (- periodically test restoring a backup) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 519.00 Td (If someone deletes data before the daily backup runs, restoring the previous backup) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 505.00 Td (may lose legitimate work done after that backup. For busy offices, consider two) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 491.00 Td (backups per day.) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 469.00 Td (Example for 1:00 PM and 8:00 PM daily:) Tj ET
BT /F3 8.8 Tf 54 439.00 Td (0 13 * * * /opt/recordkeeper/backup-recordkeeper.sh >> /opt/recordkeeper/backu) Tj ET
BT /F3 8.8 Tf 54 427.00 Td (ps/cron.log 2>&1) Tj ET
BT /F3 8.8 Tf 54 415.00 Td (0 20 * * * /opt/recordkeeper/backup-recordkeeper.sh >> /opt/recordkeeper/backu) Tj ET
BT /F3 8.8 Tf 54 403.00 Td (ps/cron.log 2>&1) Tj ET
BT /F2 13 Tf 54 367.00 Td (9. Recovery Scenario: Data Was Deleted) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 336.00 Td (If someone signs in and deletes important data, act quickly.) Tj ET
BT /F2 11 Tf 54 308.00 Td (Step 1: Stop The Backend) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 281.00 Td (Stop the app backend so users cannot continue changing data during recovery:) Tj ET
BT /F3 8.8 Tf 54 251.00 Td (sudo systemctl stop recordkeeper-backend) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 223.00 Td (Nginx can remain running, but the app will not work properly until the backend is) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 209.00 Td (started again.) Tj ET
BT /F2 11 Tf 54 181.00 Td (Step 2: Save The Damaged Database) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 154.00 Td (Before restoring, save the current damaged database. This may help with investigation) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 140.00 Td (or manual recovery of records entered after the last good backup.) Tj ET
BT /F3 8.8 Tf 54 110.00 Td (pg_dump "postgresql://postgres:postgres@localhost:5432/recordkeeper" > /opt/re) Tj ET
BT /F3 8.8 Tf 54 98.00 Td (cordkeeper/backups/damaged_recordkeeper_$\(date +%F_%H-%M-%S\).sql) Tj ET
endstream
endobj
8 0 obj
<< /Length 2140 >>
stream
BT /F2 11 Tf 54 732.00 Td (Step 3: Choose The Backup To Restore) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 705.00 Td (List available backups:) Tj ET
BT /F3 8.8 Tf 54 675.00 Td (ls -lh /opt/recordkeeper/backups/recordkeeper_*.sql.gz) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 647.00 Td (Choose the latest backup from before the deletion happened.) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 625.00 Td (Example:) Tj ET
BT /F3 8.8 Tf 54 595.00 Td (/opt/recordkeeper/backups/recordkeeper_2026-06-24_20-00-00.sql.gz) Tj ET
BT /F2 11 Tf 54 561.00 Td (Step 4: Drop And Recreate The Database) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 534.00 Td (This removes the damaged production database and creates a clean empty database.) Tj ET
BT /F3 8.8 Tf 54 504.00 Td (sudo -u postgres dropdb recordkeeper) Tj ET
BT /F3 8.8 Tf 54 492.00 Td (sudo -u postgres createdb recordkeeper) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 464.00 Td (Only run these commands after you have selected the backup and saved the damaged) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 450.00 Td (database.) Tj ET
BT /F2 11 Tf 54 422.00 Td (Step 5: Restore The Selected Backup) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 395.00 Td (Restore from the compressed backup:) Tj ET
BT /F3 8.8 Tf 54 365.00 Td (gunzip -c /opt/recordkeeper/backups/recordkeeper_2026-06-24_20-00-00.sql.gz | ) Tj ET
BT /F3 8.8 Tf 54 353.00 Td (psql "postgresql://postgres:postgres@localhost:5432/recordkeeper") Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 325.00 Td (Replace the filename with the backup you selected.) Tj ET
BT /F2 11 Tf 54 297.00 Td (Step 6: Start The Backend) Tj ET
BT /F3 8.8 Tf 54 262.00 Td (sudo systemctl start recordkeeper-backend) Tj ET
BT /F3 8.8 Tf 54 250.00 Td (sudo systemctl status recordkeeper-backend) Tj ET
BT /F2 11 Tf 54 216.00 Td (Step 7: Verify The App) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 189.00 Td (Open the LAN app in a browser and check:) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 167.00 Td (- login works) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 153.00 Td (- dashboard loads) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 139.00 Td (- search shows expected records) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 125.00 Td (- reports load) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 111.00 Td (- add/edit workflow works) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 97.00 Td (- admin settings load) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 75.00 Td (Also check the backend health endpoint:) Tj ET
endstream
endobj
9 0 obj
<< /Length 2525 >>
stream
BT /F3 8.8 Tf 54 722.00 Td (curl http://localhost:3000/api/health) Tj ET
BT /F2 13 Tf 54 686.00 Td (10. Important Recovery Notes) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 655.00 Td (Restoring a backup returns the database to the exact state at the backup time.) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 633.00 Td (Example:) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 611.00 Td (- backup time: 8:00 PM yesterday) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 597.00 Td (- deletion time: 4:00 PM today) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 583.00 Td (- restored backup: 8:00 PM yesterday) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 561.00 Td (In this case, all legitimate work entered between 8:00 PM yesterday and 4:00 PM today) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 547.00 Td (will not be present after restore.) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 525.00 Td (To preserve evidence or recover later entries manually, keep the damaged dump created) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 511.00 Td (in Step 2.) Tj ET
BT /F2 13 Tf 54 481.00 Td (11. Test Restore Without Touching Production) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 450.00 Td (A backup is only useful if it can be restored. Periodically test one backup into a) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 436.00 Td (separate test database:) Tj ET
BT /F3 8.8 Tf 54 406.00 Td (sudo -u postgres dropdb --if-exists recordkeeper_restore_test) Tj ET
BT /F3 8.8 Tf 54 394.00 Td (sudo -u postgres createdb recordkeeper_restore_test) Tj ET
BT /F3 8.8 Tf 54 382.00 Td (gunzip -c /opt/recordkeeper/backups/recordkeeper_2026-06-24_20-00-00.sql.gz | ) Tj ET
BT /F3 8.8 Tf 54 370.00 Td (psql "postgresql://postgres:postgres@localhost:5432/recordkeeper_restore_test") Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 342.00 Td (Check tables exist:) Tj ET
BT /F3 8.8 Tf 54 312.00 Td (psql "postgresql://postgres:postgres@localhost:5432/recordkeeper_restore_test") Tj ET
BT /F3 8.8 Tf 54 300.00 Td ( -c "\\dt") Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 272.00 Td (When finished:) Tj ET
BT /F3 8.8 Tf 54 242.00 Td (sudo -u postgres dropdb recordkeeper_restore_test) Tj ET
BT /F2 13 Tf 54 206.00 Td (12. Quick Emergency Checklist) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 175.00 Td (Use this checklist during an actual deletion incident:) Tj ET
BT /F3 8.8 Tf 54 145.00 Td (1. Tell users to stop using the app.) Tj ET
BT /F3 8.8 Tf 54 133.00 Td (2. Stop backend: sudo systemctl stop recordkeeper-backend) Tj ET
BT /F3 8.8 Tf 54 121.00 Td (3. Dump damaged DB for investigation.) Tj ET
BT /F3 8.8 Tf 54 109.00 Td (4. Pick latest good backup before deletion.) Tj ET
BT /F3 8.8 Tf 54 97.00 Td (5. Drop and recreate recordkeeper database.) Tj ET
BT /F3 8.8 Tf 54 85.00 Td (6. Restore selected backup.) Tj ET
BT /F3 8.8 Tf 54 73.00 Td (7. Start backend.) Tj ET
endstream
endobj
